cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI 

The paper deals with the use of unsupervised learning methods on urban images for geographical knowledge discovery. This involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for feature extraction and principal component analysis (PCA) for dimensionality reduction. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also deals with geographical processes and urban analytics, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The use of unsupervised learning methods and the exploration of the latent space suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
